	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Fran</placeName> <date>May 29&#8212;<lb/>1862</date></p>
				<p>Dr. <addressee>Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Revd. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I beg to for&#45;<lb/>&#45;ward the enclosed to<lb/> you&#44; and would very<lb/> much like it inserted<lb/> in your next issue<lb/> and the Jewish words<lb/> put in Hebrew Letters.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have sent a<lb/> copy of the article to<lb/> <persName>Dr Eckman</persName> of the &#8220;Gleaner&#8221;<lb/> in this city&#44; with a<lb/> request that he also<lb/> would publish it&#8212;</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>in this work&#39;s issue.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If you insert<lb/> the article please to<lb/> forward a number to<lb/> me under cover to<lb/> <persName>Dr. Eckman</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">To</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">M<hi rend="underline">me</hi> Waldon Cohen</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">San Francisco</hi></placeName></p>
				<p>I am wife to the <persName>Mr<lb/> Cohen</persName> who wrote to<lb/> you from <placeName>Auburn Cal</placeName><lb/> some years since on<lb/> Chinese Jews&#8212;and<lb/> am sister to <persName>Mrs S.<lb/> Benjamin</persName> late of <placeName>Montreal</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p><placeName>Canada</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have the honour<lb/> to remain sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yrs with gt. respect</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Sophie Waldon Cohen</persName></p>
		</body>
